# On the VPS: copy to .env.production in the app directory (chmod 600, chown deploy).
# The bundled systemd unit uses EnvironmentFile=-/var/www/epicfinance/.env.production so variables
# are injected before Node starts. systemd treats # as starting a comment and may expand $ in values—
# if your password contains those characters, keep mail secrets in this file only (no EnvironmentFile)
# or use an app password without #/$, or set SMTP_ENV_FILE to a path loaded by Node/dotenv only.
#
# Optional: SMTP_ENV_FILE=/etc/epicfinance.env — extra file merged after .env.production (override).
#
# Optional SEO: canonical URLs, Open Graph og:url (default https://epicfinance.co.nz if unset).
# NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_URL=https://epicfinance.co.nz
#
# Local development (next dev): Next loads .env.local — copy the SMTP_* lines there to test forms locally
# (do not commit .env.local; it is gitignored).
#
# If the contact form returns 500: check SMTP_PASS (Zoho app-specific password) and restart:
#   sudo systemctl restart epicfinance-nextjs
# Server logs: journalctl -u epicfinance-nextjs -n 80 --no-pager
#   (look for "smtp: MAIL_SMTP_NOT_CONFIGURED" with hasHost/hasUser/hasPass, or "smtp: sendMail failed")
#
# Zoho: 465 + SSL (default below) or 587 + STARTTLS — set SMTP_PORT=587
# Optional override: SMTP_SECURE=true|false (defaults: 465 → secure, 587 → STARTTLS)
# Optional From header (default is SMTP_USER). Use RFC5322 form for a display name:
# SMTP_FROM=Epic Finance <admin@epicfinance.co.nz>
SMTP_HOST=smtppro.zoho.com
SMTP_PORT=465
SMTP_USER=admin@epicfinance.co.nz
SMTP_PASS=
# Default inbox for contact form (/api/contact) and fallbacks below:
CONTACT_TO=admin@epicfinance.co.nz
# Optional: separate inboxes (default is CONTACT_TO):
# COMPLAINTS_TO=compliance@epicfinance.co.nz
# LOAN_APPLICATION_TO=applications@epicfinance.co.nz
#
# Form API routes (same Next.js process as the site): /api/contact, /api/complaints, /api/loan-application
#
# --- If mail never arrives (checklist) ---
# 1) File exists: ls -la /var/www/epicfinance/.env.production (owned/readable by deploy)
# 2) Zoho: use app-specific password for SMTP_PASS if required; SMTP_USER = full mailbox email
# 3) After any edit: sudo systemctl restart epicfinance-nextjs
# 4) Logs: sudo journalctl -u epicfinance-nextjs -n 120 --no-pager
#    - "smtp: message accepted" + messageId → provider took the message (check spam / CONTACT_TO inbox)
#    - "smtp: sendMail failed" + responseCode → auth, TLS, or port (try 465 vs 587)
# 5) Browser: Network tab → POST /api/contact → Response JSON: "code" MAIL_SMTP_NOT_CONFIGURED = this file missing or SMTP_HOST/SMTP_USER/SMTP_PASS blank → fill and sudo systemctl restart epicfinance-nextjs ; MAIL_SEND_FAILED = journalctl smtp errors (Zoho auth/port)
